cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on applying machine learning to distributed private data, using differentially-private gradients to minimize the fitness cost of the model. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper also deals with privacy concerns, specifically differential privacy, in the context of machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the trade-off between privacy and utility in machine learning, which involves considerations of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper deals with distributed datasets owned by multiple data owners, which involves database management and querying. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper applies machine learning algorithms to real-world problems (determining interest rates of loans and detecting credit card frauds), which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence.
